{
  "texts": [
    "Enabling largescale processing of patent data is not only critical in the patent space.",
    "Learning-based molecular generation methods can benefit from Pat-CID, as a large corpus of 13.8M unique chemical structures can be used for training models [37] [38] [39].",
    "In conclusion, PatCID is a chemical-structure database sourced from patent publications.",
    "Leveraging state-of-the-art document understanding models, PatCID surpasses automatically-generated databases in terms of data quality by substantial margins.",
    "With its extensive document coverage, PatCID can even compete with goldstandard manually-curated databases."
  ]
}